Summary of colocalization analysis

Silva Kasela

06/01/2020

For colocalization analysis including eQTL data for genes that have an eQTL implicated in

  • blood cell traits (EFO parent category = Hematological measurement)
  • pulmonary function traits (EFO parent category = Pulmonary function measurement)
  • respiratory system disease (EFO parent category = Respiratory disease)

Colocalization analysis:

  • Using both the standard method and coloc-cond/mask
    • When using coloc-cond/mask, then using method = mask in the GWAS dataset and LD from the matching 1000G population (for example, if discovery population is of European ancestry, then using 1000G CEU population for calculating LD)
    • When using coloc-cond/mask, then using method = single in the eQTL dataset if the eGene does not have multiple independent eVaraints, otherwise using conditional p-values (all the eGenes tested in coloc had only one independent eVariant)
  • Coloc in 500-kb region centered on lead eQTL (+/-250 kb from the lead variant)
  • Priors p1 = 1e-4, p2 = 1e-4, p3 = 5e-6
